  <h2>The Impact:</h2>

  <div class="side-by-side">
    <div>
      <p class="big">A Tournament That Dominated Viewership</p>
      <p>
        With 811K Hours Watched and 234K Peak Viewers across just four hours of
        airtime, this became the second-most popular BoomTV tournament ever and
        third-most popular Fortnite event of 2023.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div>
      <p class="big">Fortnite’s Biggest Influencers Amplified the Event</p>
      <p>
        Massive influencers, including Mongraal and Clix, were the top three
        most-watched streamers, driving engagement far beyond the official
        broadcast. The official Fortnite channel wasn’t even in the top
        10—proving the tournament’s success was powered by community-driven
        hype.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div>
      <p class="big">The Most-Watched Fortnite Tournament Post-OG Update</p>
      <p>
        The Reunion was the most successful competitive Fortnite event following
        the OG update, surpassing other high-profile tournaments in viewership
        and prize pool impact, cementing BoomTV as one of the premier Fortnite
        tournament organizers, while boosting Epic's visibility on the OG event
        far beyond their goals.
      </p>
